          <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Arts Require Timely Service Act of 2016 or the ARTS Act of 2016</strong></p> <p> This bill amends the Immigration and Nationality Act to require the Department of Homeland Security (DHS) to adjudicate O and P visa petitions (nonimmigrant visas for aliens with extraordinary ability or achievement, and artists and entertainers) within 14 days after receiving such petitions and related documents. </p> <p>The bill grants premium visa processing without charge to a petitioner that is a nonprofits arts organization if DHS does not meet the deadline for adjudicating a visa petition.</p>]]></text>
        </item>
      </billSummaries>
